OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FThere will be some bright or
OL,6,Fsunny spells on Sunday, although a
OL,7,Fscattering of showers are also likely,
OL,8,Fone or two of which could be heavy
OL,9,Fwith some hail and thunder. The strong
OL,10,Fand gusty southwesterly wind will
OL,11,Fslowly ease.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FShowers dying out during the
OL,14,Fevening leaving a dry night with clear
OL,15,Fspells. Turning chilly with frost
OL,16,Fdeveloping in rural areas. The odd
OL,17,Fmist patch forming in the lighter
OL,18,Fwinds.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
